climbs.name: You Can't Get There From Here

content.description: Sharp, thin, and delicate moves may get you to the arete.  Limited handholds and crummy feet make this a tough climb, it eases up a lot after the third bolt.  The fourth bolt and piton are shared with the route I Just Wanna Be In The Guidebook.
content.location: Around the corner (left) of the route I Just Wanna Be In The Guidebook.  You can see three of the four bolts from the base.

content.description: A little bit more difficult than it looks but climbs nicely and has adequate protection.  A nice warmup for the more difficult routes in Cactus Flower West area.
content.protection: One piton, small to medium cams, nuts
content.location: The first route one will see when approaching the area and just to the right of the route Arizona 7.  You can see the piton from the base.

climbs.name: I Just Wanna Be in the Guidebook!
climbs.fa: Ed "the Davis", Tom "NC" McMillan, Bob Jacobs '85

content.description: Airy climbing out left past bolts above a roof leads to vertical moves to summit. The final moves are grainy .
content.protection: bolts, top rap anchor may need replacing
content.location: right of alcove with "You Can't Get There From Here" and "Cactus Flower" is an obvious face. The right line is "Arizona 7", the left trending line is "Guidebook".

content.description: Climb short wide crack to nice stance and clip bolt.  Upwards yields junky rock but decent protection.  Traverse right to second bolt (crux) and upwards to piton and top of climb.  *A large horn-like feature came off on lead and resulted in a nice fall.  The route is safer now but contains some crumbly granite.
content.location: Located just left of You Can't Get There From Here.  You can see both bolts from the base.

climbs.name: Cactus Flower
climbs.fa: FA (A.0) Dana Hollister, Patty Hollister '77, FFA Chuck Parker, Dennis Abbink '78

content.description: A short chimney leads to a stiff short hand and fist crack. Originally named "No guts No Glory because of Dana's A.0 move(s).
content.location: left side of alcove, the crack arches to right at top.

content.description: Typical thin moves on granite gives way to nice cracks.  Trend slightly right to clip the shared piton of Unnamed Route to the top.
content.location: Just to the left of Unnamed Route, easily identified by two bolts near base.

content.description: A west facing variant to Cactus Flower east, yet holds the namesake of the area.
